Name: Tabletop 7Pieces Hemming Foot Set
Short description: Durable and handy sewing accessory for everyday use.
Description:
Hemming feet are used to create neat, professional hems on fabric. 
Wide hem feet
Can create double-folded hems without the need for pinning, pressing, or marking. The foot has a guide with a brick folder that pre-folds the fabric before it reaches the presser foot. 
Hemmer feet
Can be used to create hems on light to medium weight fabrics, such as scarves, light skirts, or dresses. 
Here are some tips for using a hemming foot:
  • Adjust the needle position to the left and elongate the stitch length. 
  • Iron medium weight fabrics before feeding them through the presser foot. 
  • Use your fingers to gently guide the fabric through the presser foot. 
Seven sizes of hemming attachments for domestic tabletop sewing machines : 2/8, 3/8, 4/8, 5/8, 6/8, 7/8 and 8/8 of an inch respectively.

Description: https://youtube.com/shorts/qsyXkDmITlk?feature=share The walking foot is often described as a sewing machine foot that evenly feeds layers of fabric and batting through the machine while quilting. The foot grips onto the top layer of fabric and helps move it under the needle at the same pace that the machine's feed dogs are moving the bottom layer of fabric. This amazing foot have large plastic wheels inside them to help keep all layers even so you get nice, flat edges. The walking foot keeps fabric and batting layers together while quilting. It is your best friend when machine quilting straight lines and large, gently curved lines. Good for sewing multiple layers of fabrics without skipped stitches, for example when sewing peplum dresses.
Categories: Sewing Machine Foot > Industrial Foots & Attachments, Sewing Machine Foot

Name: Blackhead Manual Machine Teflon Foot
Short description: Durable and handy sewing accessory for everyday use.
Description:
A Teflon foot, also known as a non-stick foot, is used for sewing fabrics that tend to stick to a regular presser foot, such as vinyl, leather, suede, and plastic. The Teflon coating on the bottom of the foot allows the fabric to glide smoothly, preventing it from tugging against the foot. 
Here are some uses for a Teflon foot:
  • Home decor projects: When making home decor projects that use upholstery fabrics with backings 
  • Clear windows: When sewing vinyl for a clear window, a standard foot can drag and make it difficult to get good stitching 
  • Slippery fabrics: When sewing slippery fabrics, a Teflon foot makes it easy
Categories: Sewing Machine Foot > Manual Blackhead Foots, Sewing Machine Foot

Name: Blackhead Manual Machine Compensating Foot
Short description: Durable and handy sewing accessory for everyday use.
Description:
A compensating presser foot is used for sewing even stitches along the edge of fabric, top stitching, and more: 
  • Sewing even stitches
    A compensating foot can create even stitches 1/16 in from the edge of the fabric. 
  • Top stitching
    A compensating foot is useful for top stitching close to the edge of a zipper or bag. 
  • Sewing through different thicknesses
    A compensating foot can go over different thicknesses of fabric. The larger toe of the foot sits against the feed dogs while the fabric sits under the foot. 
  • Stabilizing stitching
    A compensating foot can stabilize stitching 1.5 mm to the right or left of a thick seam. 
  • Using as a seam guide
    A compensating foot can be used with a gauge to get an accurate seam allowance.
Categories: Sewing Machine Foot > Manual Blackhead Foots, Sewing Machine Foot

Name: Singer 14HD854 Heavy Duty Serger
Short description: Durable and handy sewing accessory for everyday use.
Description:
Heavy duty metal frame and larger cutting knife provides extra durability and cuts through thicker fabrics with ease. For your convenience, your machine will arrive pre-threaded. Accessories included are located in the storage area at the front of your machine.  
Built-In Stitches (8)
Choose from a variety of stitches for basic sewing, decorative sewing, and more
Adjustable Stitch Length (+)
Customize the appearance of a stitch by increasing or decreasing the distance between stitches. Use this function for various stitch techniques like applique, basting and more.
Adjustable Stitch Width ()
The size of the stitch from left to right is adjustable, to make the stitch sew narrower or wider as desired.
Thread Capability (2-3-4)
Choose from seams finishes, hem finishes and decorative edges thanks to a variety of stitch combinations available.
Color Coded Threading System (+)
Threading path for each thread is indicated with a specific color to simplify the threading process. Handy reference diagrams are also included right on the machine.
Differential Feed (+)
Controls the ratio of movement between the front and back sections of the feed teeth. Use this to help remove distortion from seams in stretchy fabrics or puckers from seams in lightweight or silky fabrics.
Built-In Rolled Hem (4)
Just slide a lever to easily convert the machine for rolled hem sewing - no need to change stitch plate
Movable Upper Knife (+)
Upper knife can be engaged to trim excess seam allowance as you sew, or it can be rolled out of the way for special techniques like flatlocking or anytime when you don't want the machine to trim
Heavy Duty Metal Frame (+)
The machine's interior frame is metal, providing long lasting durability
High Speed Stitching (1300/min)
Professional speed for faster results.
Speed Control (Digital)
Set the maximum sewing speed of the machine
LED Lighting (+)
Long lasting LED lighting provides bright illumination and stays cool to the touch
Free Arm (+)
Slide off the Removable Storage Compartment for access to the free arm, making it easy to sew trouser hems, sleeve cuffs and other smaller or tubular projects
Extra High Presser Foot Lifter (+)
Presser foot has an extra high position available to accommodate thick fabrics.

Sew with ease for almost any project with the Singer Promise 1409 Sewing Machine! With basic, decorative and buttonhole stitching included, this machine offers all the essential features you'll need and is perfect for sewing beginners. The Singer Promise 1408 can sew many layers of fabric and take on even heavy fabrics, making it ideal for a wide range of sewing patterns and projects. There are eight built-in stitches available, so whether your purpose is fashion design, garment repairs, home décor or quilting, this machine has you covered! The stitches include buttonhole, straight, zigzag, blind hems, rick rack, scallop and rampart. Set-up is easier than ever with this machine, as you have an automatic bobbin winder and simple machine threading. There is a reverse lever to allow for automatic stitch locking. In the accessory storage drawer, you will find four presser feet: general, buttonhole, button sewing and zipper. These are easily removable, making it effortless to switch them over or to create a free arm for stitching in hard-to-reach areas. Machine features:

Name: 6in1 Stitch & Stick Guide
Short description: Durable and handy sewing accessory for everyday use.
Description: The 6-in-1 Stick ‘n Stitch Guide is a truly multi-function tool that will make sewing even the most difficult and demanding applications of thread to fabric a breeze. The stitch guide itself is a two-piece interlocking plastic foot. They can be used together or separately depending on your stitching application. Connection with your sewing machine is accomplished by a renewable adhesive attached permanently to the bottom of each foot. Just remove the seam guide feet from your machine when you’re done. They leave no adhesive residue. Washing the adhesive surface on the guide foot with dish soap renews the surface and its adhesive properties. The shapes and edges of each guide foot makes it perfect for a multitude of sewing applications. The included grid template measures placement from the needle position and ensures that the stitch guide is always just where we want it. So, how’s it used? Unlike other seam guides, the Stick ‘n Stitch Guide does way more than provide a single seam allowance. In fact its innovative design provides us with six different primary applications. 1. The two sections can be used either singly or together for straight stitching 2. We can place one foot on either side of the needle for fast, error free quilt strips or precision placement top stitches. 3. Place the curve side up in a position in front of the presser foot for outer curves. 4. Place the curve side down in a position in front of the presser foot for inner curves 5. Straight stitch on the right side. 6. Straight stitch on the left side.

Name: Tailor’s Clapper

Description: A tailor's clapper is a flat block of hardwood, often rounded on the ends with routed grooves along the sides for finger holds. It works by absorbing the steam applied to a seam, and locking in the heat. As you press down on the seam with the clapper, the pressure sets the seam flat as the fabric cools. So, if you like to have flat seams when you sew (I know I do) then this humble tool can help you! Name: Rectangle Rhinestone Flipper
Short description: Durable and handy sewing accessory for everyday use.
Description:
With just a shake, flat back stones will turn right side up, quickly and easily!

The textured surface design of the tray uses friction to flip your stones just like magic!

They'll turn flat side down ready to be put into place, saving you time and aggravation.

The Magical Tray is designed for use with your favorite flat back stones up to size ss12.

1. Place stones in tray. A small number of stones works best.

2. Shake gently in a circular motion until the stones begin to turn over.

If static prevents small beads from moving smoothly, nudge them closer to the center of the tray and try again.

When you learn to shake the tray correctly most stones will quickly turn over, however, even after shaking properly some beads could remain upside-down.

Intended for use with flat back rhinestones ss12 and smaller.

https://youtube.com/shorts/TIuR29SFYds?feature=share

Name: Big Wooden Bead Spinner
Short description: Durable and handy sewing accessory for everyday use.
Description:
It is basically a bowl on a spindle. The spindle allows the bowl to spin. So, when you fill it with seed beads, you can spin it around.

Centrifugal force pushes the beads into a stream at the edges of the bowl. So, if you stick a piece of wire, or a long needle into these beads, then a steady stream of beads will flow up your wire/needle and thread.

You can use a bead spinner any time you want to thread a large quantity of seed beads.

Name: Singer Heavy Duty 6335 Denim Sewing Machine
Short description: Durable and handy sewing accessory for everyday use.
Description:
With a heavy duty metal frame and powerful motor for enhanced piercing power, the SINGER® HD6335M Denim sewing machine is a true workhorse. Sew jeans hems and thick fabric layers with ease. Key stitches for all types of fabric, plus an easy one-step buttonhole, offer loads of creative options as well.

Main features of Singer HD 6335 Denim:

  • 32 sewing programmes: 6 utility stitches, 11 stretch and 14 decorative stitches, 1-step buttonholer.
  • Extra High Sewing Speed – 1,100 Stitches Per Minute
  • Metal chassis made of light alloy, solid and strong but comfortable to transport.
  • The jam-proof steel rotary hook ensures a silent and consistent functioning.
  • The feed dog disengagement lever allows you to free-hand sew as mending and free-motion embroidery.
  • Easy bobbin top loading: it allows to see the residual thread and a quick replacement of the bobbin.
  • Adjustable thread tension to adapt it to any sewing technique and/or fabric.
  • Adjustable presser foot pressure to sew any material perfectly.
  • Extra lifting of the presser foot: it allows to insert and sew even extra-large thicknesses.
  • Adjustable needle position for visible stitching, special applications such as flat fell seam and zip fastening.
  • Stitch width adjustable up to 6 mm for all programs.
  • Stitch length adjustable up to 4 mm.
  • Stitching with twin needle, to create fabulous embroideries also in 2 colors.
  • Sewing surface with scratch-proof stainless steel plate.
  • Led light.
  • Automatic needle threader, it speeds up threading and eliminates waste of time.
  • Stretch stitches, also for sewing stretch garments with tailored results.

Name: Gravity Steam Iron Thermostat Set
Short description: Durable and handy sewing accessory for everyday use.
Description:
The main function of thermostat in an electric iron is to make sure that the iron doesn’t get too hot if it is left unattended to for a period of time. When electric current is passed through a coil in an electric iron, the coil becomes very hot. Through conduction the heat is transferred to the flat base plate of the electric iron which is used to iron our clothes . However, the heating element continues to get hotter so far there is continuous drawing of electricity from the power supply. This result into a lot of energy wastage, cloths ruin and in the worst scenario, cause nasty accident. At this point, thermostat comes in because it is important that the iron doesn’t heat up to temperature that is hazardous.
  • Precise Temperature Control: The Thermostat is specially designed , providing precise temperature control for your ironing needs.
  • Optimal Ironing Results: Achieve perfect results with the ability to set and maintain the ideal temperature, ensuring smooth and wrinkle-free ironing on various fabrics.
  • Easy Installation: Simple to install, the thermostat allows you to upgrade your iron quickly, so you can get back to tackling your ironing tasks efficiently.

Name: Industrial Special Cording Rolling Foot
Short description: Durable and handy sewing accessory for everyday use.
Description:
An Industrial Special Cording Rolling Foot, also known as a cording foot or piping foot, is used to sew cording, piping, or zippers neatly and smoothly, especially on industrial sewing machines, and it is designed to prevent fabric slippage and feed difficult materials. 
  • Roller: The foot features a roller (or rollers) that helps to feed the fabric smoothly and prevent slippage, especially when sewing over seams or uneven surfaces. 
  • Versatility: Some models can be used as zipper feet, cording feet, or even standard presser feet. 
  • Smooth Sewing: The roller design ensures a smooth and even feed, leading to professional-looking results. 
  • Fabric Handling: It's ideal for working with difficult fabrics that can be prone to puckering or slipping. 
  • Precise Seam Placement: The foot helps to achieve precise seam placement, especially when sewing close to piping.
Categories: Sewing Machine Foot > Industrial Foots & Attachments, Sewing Machine Foot

Name: Industrial Adjustable Roller Unilateral Invisible Zipper Foot
Short description: Durable and handy sewing accessory for everyday use.
Description:
An industrial roller unilateral invisible zipper foot is used for sewing invisible zippers on garments, allowing for a professional, seamless finish by guiding the zipper teeth and ensuring the needle stitches close to them.  This specialized presser foot is designed to sew invisible zippers, which are coil zippers where the elements are hidden behind the tape, making the zipper virtually invisible when closed. 
  • Benefits:
    • Precision: The foot allows for accurate stitching close to the zipper teeth, resulting in a neat and professional finish. 
    • Seamless Zipper: The foot helps create a seamless appearance, as the zipper is hidden and the seam is barely visible. 
    • Versatility: It's suitable for various garments like pants, dresses, skirts, blouses, and trousers, as well as home furnishings like pillowcases and cushions. 
  • How to use:
    • Attach the foot to your sewing machine, ensuring it is positioned correctly relative to the zipper teeth. 
    • Set your needle position to the middle to avoid striking the foot. 
    • Sew along the zipper, keeping the needle as close to the zipper teeth as possible. 
  • Other uses:
    While primarily designed for invisible zippers, a zipper foot can also be used for sewing piping or cording, and attaching other elements where sewing close to a raised edge is necessary.
Categories: Sewing Machine Foot > Industrial Foots & Attachments, Sewing Machine Foot

Name: Industrial Sewing machine Wide Bias Attachment (Waist Band Folder)
Short description: Durable and handy sewing accessory for everyday use.
Description:
An industrial sewing machine wide bias attachment, also known as a bias binder, is used to automatically fold and attach bias tape to fabric edges, creating a professional, finished look for hems, necklines, and other edges. 
  • Function:
    The attachment folds the bias tape around the fabric edge, and guides it into the stitching area, ensuring a clean and consistent finish. 
  • Benefits:
    • Speed and Efficiency: Automates the process of attaching bias tape, saving time and effort compared to manual methods. 
    • Precision: Creates uniform, professional-looking finishes. 
    • Versatility: Suitable for various projects, including clothing, quilting, and home décor. 
      How to Use:
      1. Prepare the Bias Tape: Cut the bias tape to the desired length. 
      2. Attach the Bias Binder: Install the bias binder foot on your industrial sewing machine. 
      3. Feed the Bias Tape: Feed the bias tape through the channels of the binder foot. 
      4. Sew: Stitch along the edge of the fabric, with the bias tape folded and guided by the binder foot. 
  • This bias attachment will give you an output of 1 inch tape suitable for cuffs and waist bands.

Name: Domestic Free Motion Embroidery Quilting Presser Foot
Short description: Durable and handy sewing accessory for everyday use.
Description:
• Enhanced Visibility & Control: The Free Motion Spring Foot offers exceptional visibility and control during free motion quilting or embroidery. With its open front design, you can easily see your work and follow intricate designs in the fabric. This makes it perfect for executing stippling, meandering, and thread painting techniques with precision and ease.
  • Prevents Fabric Lifting & Thread Breakage: The spring action of the foot provides an added advantage by preventing the fabric from lifting with the needle as you stitch. This feature is particularly beneficial when working with specialty or heavier threads, as it helps eliminate thread breakage.
  • Versatile & Customizable: With the Free Motion Spring Foot, you have the freedom to sew any pattern according to your imagination. It allows you to unleash your creativity and experiment with various stitching techniques. Whether you want to create intricate designs or add personal touches to your quilts or fabric projects, this foot provides the versatility you need to bring your ideas to life.
  • Premium Materials: Crafted with high-quality steel, this presser foot offers exceptional durability and long-lasting performance. The sturdy construction ensures it can withstand the rigors of frequent use, making it an ideal choice for all your sewing requirements.
  • Wide Compatibility: Suitable for most low shank sewing machines, including Singer, Brother, Janome, Juki, Babylock, Elna, Kenmore, White, Necchi, Simplicity, Euro-Pro, New Home, and more. Also Blackhead Manual Machine.
